    "client_msg_id": "0310d5f3-efbb-4abf-b85b-183767a92768",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Yes <@UCGAK10LS>, I have an iPad Pro with pencil for the same thing. The feel of the Remarkable is dramatically better. Has a soft wearable tip and the surface has some friction. It also feels lighter. And it's much less distracting. It has none of the noise and interruptions of my iPad. If I could have just one, I'd go with Remarkable hands down. There are a few things that the iPad is great at that I'll keep using it for (marking up screenshots, 3d stuff, facetime/zoom), but for thinking now it's all about the remarkable for me.",
    "user": "UMVFWPZ36",
